<div class="docs-content__header">
  <span class="docs-content__eyebrow">Get Started</span>
  <h1 class="docs-content__title">Quick Start</h1>
  <p class="docs-content__description">Create your first project, staff it with an agent, and run a task — all in under five minutes.</p>
</div>

<div class="prose">
  <h2 id="create-a-project">Create a Project</h2>
  <p>After signing in, click <strong>New Project</strong> from the dashboard. Give your project a name — this is the isolated workspace where all your agents, goals, and tasks will live.</p>
  <p>Director automatically seeds the project with default role categories and built-in skills so you can start staffing immediately.</p>

  <h2 id="set-up-a-role">Set Up a Role</h2>
  <p>Navigate to <strong>Roles</strong> and create your first role. Pick a role category (e.g., Engineering) and give it a title like "Code Assistant". Write a <strong>job spec</strong> describing what the agent should do — this becomes part of the system prompt the agent receives.</p>
  <p>Assign skills from the project's skill library to give the agent specific capabilities. Skills are injected into the agent's context on every execution.</p>

  <h2 id="configure-an-adapter">Configure an Adapter</h2>
  <p>A role without an adapter is just a position on the org chart. To make it a live agent, configure an adapter:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Claude Code</strong> — run Claude CLI locally with streaming output and session resumption. Set the model (e.g., <code>claude-sonnet-4-20250514</code>) and you're ready.</li>
    <li><strong>HTTP API</strong> — point to any cloud-hosted agent endpoint.</li>
    <li><strong>OpenCode</strong> — use OpenCode CLI with any supported provider (OpenAI, Gemini, Groq, etc.).</li>
    <li><strong>Shell Command</strong> — run a custom script or CLI tool.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>For this quick start, Claude Code is the fastest path. Set the model and optionally configure a working directory where the agent will operate.</p>

  <h2 id="create-a-goal">Create a Goal</h2>
  <p>Go to <strong>Goals</strong> and create one — for example, "Set up project scaffolding". Assign it to your new role. Goals give agents direction and track overall progress as tasks are completed.</p>
  <p>When you assign a goal to a role that is online, Director automatically wakes the agent to start working on it.</p>

  <h2 id="assign-a-task">Assign a Task</h2>
  <p>Create a task under your goal — something concrete like "Initialize the repository with a README". Assign it to your role. Tasks are the actual units of work: the agent picks them up, executes them, and reports back.</p>
  <p>Set a priority if needed. Tasks are sorted by priority descending by default, so urgent tasks are handled first.</p>

  <h2 id="watch-it-run">Watch It Run</h2>
  <p>Once the task is assigned, Director dispatches it to the agent. Navigate to the role's detail page to see the <strong>role run</strong> — streaming output appears in real time as the agent works.</p>
  <p>When the agent finishes, the task moves to <strong>pending review</strong> (if the creator is a top-level role) or <strong>completed</strong>. Check the task's messages for output, and the role run for cost and timing details.</p>
  <p>From here, you can create more roles, build out an org chart with parent-child hierarchies, set budgets, and configure approval gates. See the guides section for deeper walkthroughs.</p>
</div>
